155
00:05:44,559 --> 00:05:45,559
What is this craziness?

156
00:05:45,559 --> 00:05:47,160
I had no idea about this at all,

157
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:50,160
but actually, what we learn here, what we view together,

158
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:53,559
is that the order in transforms is important.

159
00:05:53,559 --> 00:05:57,559
If you first do a Rotate and then Translate on the X-axis,

160
00:05:57,559 --> 00:05:59,359
the X-axis will be like this, down.

161
00:05:59,359 --> 00:06:01,559
On the other hand, if you first do a Translate,

162
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:04,359
and then you do a Rotate, it will happen like this.

163
00:06:04,359 --> 00:06:05,959
This thing is completely mind-blowing,

164
00:06:05,959 --> 00:06:08,760
that the order in Translate was important, I didn't know that,

165
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:11,359
and I think very few front-end developers know it, anyway.

166
00:06:11,359 --> 00:06:13,959
Let me know in the comments if you knew this trick or not.

